-- United Basalt Drops Most in 10 Months on Bets Building Will Slow
-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 2012-03-19T08:19:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-19/united-basalt-drops-most-in-10-months-on-bets-building-will-slow.html
United Basalt Products Ltd. (UBP) , a
Mauritian construction company, declined the most in 10 months
on bets the building industry is set for stagnation.  The  stock  fell for a second day, retreating 5.7 percent,
the most since May, to 100 rupees at 11:51 a.m. in  Port Louis . A
close at this level will be its lowest since June 2010.  “There is selling pressure on the stock,” Bhavik Desai, a
research analyst at Axys Stockbroking Ltd., said in a phone
interview from the city. “The construction sector is expected
to stagnate this year.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
